  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of professional trust by using their position as an accountant to misappropriate $25,000. Such actions undermine the integrity of financial oversight and warrant a custodial sentence to serve as a deterrent. However, several mitigating factors have been considered: the defendant has no prior criminal history and has demonstrated a willingness to take responsibility by partially repaying the stolen funds. Balancing the seriousness of the breach of trust against the defendant's record and commitment to restitution, a sentence of 12 months of incarceration is deemed appropriate.",
  "verdict": 12
}
